<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-50-0708 </DOCNO><TEXT>The steady thermal stress field on a turbine disk is investigated experimentallyby means of photothermoelastic measurements on an epoxy resin model wrappedwith carbon-coated polyester heating tape and fitted with embedded thermocouplesfor accurate temperature determination. The data obtained are presentedin graphs and shown to be in good agreement with the results of theoreticalcomputations for a plane disk. The applicability of the present testdata as a reference for disk design is indicated.</TEXT></DOC>